  "title": "SHIPPING/ STORE ASSISTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>A Shipping/Store Assistant<br /><br />i) Able handle company’s daily shipment activities & fulfill various customer shipment expectations.<br /><br />ii) Able handle company’s incoming and outgoing goods and manage company’s stock. Support daily supply chain <br />    operations and job order fulfillment.</p><p><strong>Duties and responsibilities in Shipping:</strong></p><ul><li>Pick the good at designated staging rack.</li><li>Input & update the good receive information to system for shipment.</li><li>Pack and label the good on the tray & shipping box.</li><li>Update system of shipment info and verify the special requirement and act accordingly from customer if any.</li><li>Generate the Packing Slip and Commercial invoice from system.</li><li>Prepare, communicate and co-ordinate with forwarder of the shipment collection.</li><li>Cross support to other areas and sections if necessary.</li></ul><p><strong>Duties and responsibilities in Store:</strong></p><ul><li>Perform the job issuing according to job order from internal customer.</li><li>Perform the customer order goods picking and fulfillment.</li><li>Good practices on FIFO (First In First Out) manner.</li><li>Weight/count, pack & label of components based on job requirements.</li><li>Dispatch the job order, materials & components to designated department.</li><li>Perform the physical stock take.</li><li>Prepare & delivery shipment goods to Shipping Department.</li><li>Update system of the goods movement.</li><li>Cross support to other areas and sections if necessary.</li><li>Handle ad hoc & other tasks assigned by supervisor/manager.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Able to work in fast-paced environment.</li><li>A good team player.</li><li>Some PC knowledge.</li><li>Able read, write and speak simple English.</li><li>5 days' work week.</li></ul>",
